==Starting out==
* '''Diango:''' Howdy there partner! Want to see my spinning plates? Or did ya want a holiday item back?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|About the Halloween event...}}
** '''Diango:''' Just so you know, partner, I didn't steal anything.
** '''Player:''' What? What got stolen now?
** '''Diango:''' Nothing, nothing! No wood got stolen at all. I mean, if that had happened then people might accuse a man of cutting corners with his toy production.
** '''Player:''' What?
** '''Diango:''' I'm just letting you know, just in case anyone says anything about strange noises or boxes filled with ghosts.
** '''Diango:''' Crazy stuff like that.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|You sound like you need a hand with something.}}
*** '''Player:''' You sound like you need a hand with something.
*** '''Diango:''' You know, you aren't wrong partner.
*** '''Diango:''' Can you keep a secret?
*** '''Player:''' Of course. Keeping secrets is...err, are, my middle names.
*** '''Player:''' Or at least they would be if I had middle names.
*** '''Diango:''' Are you done?
*** '''Player:''' Sure, please continue.
*** '''Diango:''' Okay, last year we had a lot of pressure when it came to Christmas. Trying to fill the orders got a little hectic, if you get my drift.
*** '''Diango:''' So, I got my workers started on the presents now, as that means everything will be nice and ready for the big day, and there'll be plenty of time left in case anything goes wrong.
*** '''Diango:''' Well, I might have run out of wood after I tried my hand at a little Construction, so I got my workers to take a little wood from Draynor Manor...
*** '''Player:''' And now someone is after you for stealing the wood?
*** '''Diango:''' No.
*** '''Diango:''' And it wasn't stealing as such; it was all for the children, you know?
*** '''Player:''' So what's happened?
*** '''Diango:''' Well, it seems like there are so many spooks attached to the wood, that the bits and pieces we made are floating about, totally packed with ghosts!
*** '''Player:''' Ghosts?
*** '''Diango:''' Ghosts.
*** '''Diango:''' And that's not all; we've got a huge, evil tree growing out of the floor now!
*** '''Diango:''' Who am I gonna call?
*** '''Player:''' Me! I ain't afraid of no ghost.
*** '''Diango:''' Partner, if you can get the ghosts out of my workshop then you're in it for a real reward!
*** '''Diango:''' Okay, here's a little something I got the professor to whip together to deal with this little problem.
*** '''Diango:''' He called it a Phantasmic Destabiliser Mark 500. I call it a Ghost Buster 500.
*** '''Player:''' Makes sense. How does it work?
*** '''Diango:''' Well, you take the Ghost Buster here, right...and you load it with a white destabiliser.
*** '''Diango:''' Then, you spray one of the possessed items with the Ghost Buster, which will force the ghost out.
*** '''Diango:''' Then, you take a look at what colour the ghost is, and load that colour destabiliser into the Ghost Buster, and spray them again.
*** '''Diango:''' There are five types of ghosts down there, and if you get rid of three of each then we should be able to make a bit of a start on the toys again.
*** '''Player:''' Okay, that sounds about right. Can I have the Ghost Buster?
*** {{tcond|If the player's inventory is full:}}
**** '''Diango:''' I will when you have enough space for it.  You will need 7 spaces for all the gear; 5 coloured destabilisers, 1 white destabiliser and the Ghost Buster.
**** '''Player:''' Okay Diango, I'll just run to the bank!
**** {{tact|end}}
*** '''Diango:''' There you go. Good hunting!
*** '''Diango:''' Whatever you do, don't cross the streams!
*** '''Player:''' What happens if I cross the streams?
*** '''Diango:''' Well, the stuff mixes into a real nasty gunk and I'll never be able to get it off the walls.
*** '''Diango:''' And whatever you do, don't forget to check upstairs and downstairs while you are there. Once a ghost has been busted it will be gone for good, so you'll need to keep looking around for them.
*** '''Diango:''' Oh, and if you can do something about that tree I'd be grateful.
*** '''Player:''' Do what about it exactly?
*** '''Diango:''' Well, if you have an axe I'm sure when it swallows you, you'll be able to make short work of its roots.
*** '''Player:''' Swallows me?
*** '''Diango:''' Only a little.
*** '''Diango:''' Look, it only does that if you annoy it, and even then it only drops you into a chamber full of roots, which you can just climb right out of.
*** '''Player:''' Still, that's a little active for a lump of wood.
*** '''Diango:''' Oh, I'm sure you'll be fine!
*** '''Diango:''' Just bring me 10 roots to show you've given it a go and I'll see what I can rustle up for you.
*** '''Player:''' You know, I'm starting to think you are taking advantage of my good nature.
*** '''Diango:''' Perish the thought! My workshop is in the basement of the abandoned house in the north of the village. If you find yourself in a sewer then you're in the wrong place.
*** '''Diango:''' Bye!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Okay...}}
*** '''Player:''' O...K...
*** '''Player:''' Well, have fun, and don't forget to take your medication!
*** '''Diango:''' Yeah, yeah.
*** {{tact|end}}
